definitions.definition: A small inlet , often saltwater , leading to the sea or to the main channel of a river , especially a river estuary .
The inner part of a port that is used as a dock for small boats.
A stream of water, typically a stream of freshwater smaller than a river ; in Australia, also used of river-sized bodies of water.

main_definition: ( British ) A small inlet , often saltwater , leading to the sea or to the main channel of a river , especially a river estuary .
secondary_definitions: ( British ) The inner part of a port that is used as a dock for small boats.
( Australia , New Zealand , Canada , US ) A stream of water, typically a stream of freshwater smaller than a river ; in Australia, also used of river-sized bodies of water.
